The Vice President and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement expressing their support for the nomination of Cathy Russell for the position of Ambassador at Large for Global Women's Issues at the Department of State. They praised Russell's dedication to promoting gender equality and her efforts in raising awareness about issues affecting military families and community colleges. Russell has a strong background in advocating for women's rights, having served as Dr. Biden's Chief of Staff and as a Senior Advisor to the Senate Foreign Relations Committee. She played a key role in drafting legislation such as the Violence Against Women Act and the International Violence Against Women Act. Russell also served on the Communications Advisory Council of Women for Women International, an organization that supports women affected by war.